        <h2>1. Overview</h2>
        <p>The app "Fokus-Flow" is a micro-utility tool designed to help users manage habits locally on their Android devices. We take your privacy seriously and process data only as described below.</p>

        <h2>2. Local Data Storage</h2>
        <p>All core functions (habit tracking, statistics, streaks) are performed offline. Your data is stored exclusively in a local database on your device and is never uploaded to our servers.</p>

        <h2>3. Third-Party Advertising (Google AdMob)</h2>
        <p>To provide this app for free, we display advertisements via Google AdMob. This service may process data such as your IP address, device identifiers (Advertising ID), and approximate location for ad delivery and fraud prevention.</p>

        <h2>4. Consent Management (Google UMP)</h2>
        <p>We use the Google User Messaging Platform (UMP) to comply with GDPR requirements. This tool allows you to grant or withdraw consent for personalized advertising at any time within the app settings.</p>

        <h2>5. Data Deletion</h2>
        <p>You can delete all local data by uninstalling the app or clearing the app cache. To manage or delete advertising data, please reset your Advertising ID in your Android system settings under "Google > Ads".</p>
